BAnjiotensin-transforming enzyme 2 (ACE2) wani abu ne mai saurin haɗuwa da huhu, jijiyoyi, zuciya, koda, da kuma ƙwayoyin hanji.
ACE2 yana hana aikin da ake amfani da shi na angiotensin-transforming enzyme (ACE) ta hanyar rage adadin angiotensin-II da kuma ƙara Ang1-7 wanda ya sa ya zama kyakkyawan magani mai mahimmanci don magance cututtukan zuciya. ACE2 kuma yana aiki a matsayin hanyar shiga cikin kwayoyin halitta don wasu cututtukan coronaviruses.
An fi kiran sigar ɗan adam na enzyme hACE2.
Angiotensin-transforming catalyst 2 shine zinc-binding metallolzyme wanda ke kan farfajiya na endothelial da sauran kwayoyin halitta.
Protein ACE2 yana da yankin N-terminal peptide M2 da kuma yankin C-terminal colectrain renal amino acid transporter.
ACE2 shine mai wucewa guda ɗaya na nau'in I membrane protein, wanda wurin da ke aiki a cikin saurin aiki ba a rufe shi a saman ƙwayoyin huhu da sauran ƙwayoyin halitta ba.
Ƙasar waje ta ACE2 ta rabu da yankin transmembrane ta wani enzyme da ake kira shades, kuma sakamakon haka an saki furotin mai narkewa a cikin jini kuma a ƙarshe an fitar da shi ta hanyar fitsari.
ACE2 yana cikin mafi yawan gabobin: ACE2 yana da alaƙa da membrane na ƙwayoyin cuta na huhu na nau'in II, wanda ya danganci ƙwayoyin cuta na ƙananan hanji, ƙwayoyin cuta na ƙaramin hanji, ƙwayoyin cuta na sassan jiki da na jijiyoyin jiki, da ƙwayoyin cuta na jijiyoyin jini.
Hakanan an sami maganganun ACE2 mRNA a cikin ƙwaƙwalwar ƙwaƙwalwar ƙwaƙwalwa, stratum, hypothylamus, da brainstorm.
Ayyukan farko na ACE2 shine aiki a matsayin mai daidaitawa na ACE.
ACE angiotensin I yana raba hormone zuwa vasokonstrikting angiotensin II.
ACE2 ya bambanta carboxylic-terminal amino acid phenylalanine (Asp-Arg-Val-Tyr-Ile-His-Pro-Phe) daga angiotensin II kuma ya hydrolyz shi zuwa vasodilator angiotensin (1-7) (H-Asp-Arg-Val-Tyr-Ile-His-Pro-OH).
ACE2 na iya ware wasu wasu wasu peptides, ciki har da [des-Arg9]-bradykinin, apelin, neurotensin, dinorphine A, da ghrelin.
ACE2 yana sarrafa musayar ƙwayar cuta na SLC6A19, wanda yake da alaƙa da amino acid mai ɗauke da shi, kuma yana da alaƙa da cututtukan zuciya.
A matsayin furotin na transmembrane, ACE2 yana aiki a matsayin babban maɓallin shigarwa a cikin ƙwayoyin cuta na wasu coronavirus, wanda ya haɗa da HCoV-NL63; SARS-CoV (wanda ke da alhakin SARS); da kuma SARS-CoV-2 (wanda ke da alhakin COVID-19).
A takaice dai, an bayyana cewa an haɗa SARS-CoV da SARS-CoV2 na spike S1 a cikin ƙwayoyin halitta na ACE2 zuwa farfajiyar ƙwayoyin halitta wanda ke haifar da endocytosis da kuma motsawar ƙwayoyin cuta da enzymes a cikin ƙwayoyin halitta.
Wannan shigarwa na buƙatar kuma priming na S protein ta hanyar TMPRSS2 mai masaukin sarin protease, wanda ke da kariya a matsayin mai yiwuwa warkarwa a halin yanzu. Wannan ya taimaka wa wasu su yi tunanin cewa rage matakan ACE2 a cikin sel na iya taimakawa wajen yaki da kamuwa da cuta.
